                                                                                                                           6                                                                                      Business Briefs
                              
	 New Delhi, March 10: The countrys temporary job market is likely to see an 18 per cent rise in hiring this year, while average salary hikes may stay in single digits, staffing firm Teamlease said. According to the survey, growth in hiring in most industries may impact the increment structure.                             
	 New Delhi, March 10: Foreign direct investment in India declined 25 per cent to $2.04 billion in January compared with $2.73 billion in the same month last year, snapping a trend of positive growth in the previous three consecutive months.                             
	 New Delhi, March 10: The Lok Sabha will take up the vote-on-account for consideration on Friday. The vote-on-account enables the government to spend for the first three months of the next financial year before the final adoption of the demands for grants next month.                             
	 London, March 10: Standard Life plc will look at increasing stake in its Indian insurance joint venture with HDFC and explore the possibility of listing the business in India.                                                                                                                          
